      "score": null,
      "comments": null,
      "author": "Beth Mole",
      "published": "2026-05-28T20:18:54Z",
      "bullets": [
        "US healthcare spends nearly 17% of GDP yet ranks last among peer nations in access, administrative efficiency, and outcomes.",
        "Systemic rejection of standardized digital health tracking and unified administrative protocols drives up operational costs and lowers care quality.",
        "Addressing this requires tech-driven systemic reforms: API interoperability, automated billing pipelines, and scalable preventive care platforms."
      ]
